        <body>
            <listPerson>
                <person sameAs="Q115903389" sex="1">
                    <persName xml:lang="sv" xml:id="n1"><forename>Anders</forename> <surname>Svensson</surname></persName>
                    <persName xml:lang="ti" xml:id="n2"><roleName type="office">ቀሺ</roleName> ሜንሶን</persName>
                    <faith type="Protestantism"/>
                    <occupation type="ecclesiastic"/>
                    <nationality type="Sweden"/>
                    <birth when="1894-04-07">7 April 1849</birth>
                    <floruit>
                        Anders Svensson, born in Nävlinge socken in <date when="1849">1849</date>, was ordained a 
                        priest in Lund in <date when="1874">1874</date>, and became a missionary for
                        Swedish Evangelical Mission in Eritrea in <date when="1877">1877</date>. He was a teacher at the school outside
                        <ref type="place" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2852Emkull">Imkullo</ref>. From 1885 to 1897, he was the head of the school, 
                        which from 1890 was located in <ref type="place" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5393Saazza">Zazega</ref>. 
                        As the chairman of the missionary conference (<foreign xml:lang="sv">missionskonferens</foreign>)
                        from 1886 to 1913, he travelled through the entire area where the SEM was active, ordaining priests and
                        consecrating churches and graveyards.
                        He is buried in Zazega. According to <ref target="#Kahassai2023"/>,
                        he was locally known as <foreign xml:lang="ti"><roleName type="office">ቀሺ</roleName> ሜንሶን</foreign>
                        (<foreign xml:lang="ti"><roleName type="office">Qašši</roleName> Menson</foreign>),
                        which is the name attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/UppQ1524o">Uppsala, Uppsala University Library, Q 15:24 o<locus target="#5r"/></ref>.
                    </floruit>
                    <death when="1928-06-04">4 June 1928</death>
                    <residence>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2852Emkull">Ǝmkullu</placeName>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5393Saazza">Ṣäʿazzäga</placeName>
                    </residence>
                </person>
                
            </listPerson>
